  "notes": "Proof authority: Lean kernel via the tracked proof-search loop (episode 9435347e), kernel_verified on the third Solve attempt. Step 1: nlinarith [hs] alone couldn't expand the needed (sqrt D - b)*(sqrt D + b) product after field_simp. Step 2: switched to linear_combination hs (the right tool for an equality goal that's a polynomial consequence of another equality), but it failed with 'ring expressions not equal' -- field_simp had rewritten one occurrence of the sqrt's argument (b^2 - 4*a*c) into a differently-ordered but equal expression (b^2 - a*4*c), and `ring` cannot see through Real.sqrt to recognize the two resulting sqrt terms as the same atom. Step 3 fixed it by `set`-ing the sqrt term to a plain variable s (with its defining equation folded into hs) *before* field_simp/linear_combination, so both tactics only ever see the opaque atom s rather than two syntactically-distinct sqrt applications. Builds on packets/elementary/algebra/quad_form_nonneg.v1.json; closes the discriminant/real-root backlog item in packets/elementary/algebra/QUEUE.md.",
